{{if .Description}}{{.Description}}{{else}}A scientific manuscript authored in MyST Markdown and rendered to PDF via Typst.{{end}}

## Getting Started

First make sure you have the lab CLI toolbox installed:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sciminds/sci/main/install.sh | sh
```

And that it's up-to-date:

```bash
sci update && sci doctor
```

```bash
cd {{.ProjectName}}/
sci proj render        # build pdfs/main.pdf
sci proj preview       # live-preview HTML server
```

Or, equivalently, call MyST directly:

```bash
npx mystmd build --pdf   # one-shot PDF build
npx mystmd start         # live-preview server
```

## Project Structure

```
{{- if eq .MdLayout "composed" }}
main.md                # the manuscript body (Intro / Methods / Results / Discussion)
sections/
    abstract.md        # short summary printed under the title block
    keypoints.md       # bulleted highlights above the abstract
    acknowledgements.md
    opendata.md        # data/code availability statement
{{- else }}
main.md                # the manuscript body + abstract/keypoints/etc. inline in frontmatter
{{- end }}
myst.yml               # MyST project config — authors, parts, exports
refs.bib               # BibTeX references — cite with {cite}`key`
figs/                  # put figures here, reference with ![](figs/foo.png)
{{- if eq .Template "lab" }}
_templates/paper/      # the local Typst template — fully editable
    paper.typ          # the actual layout — restyle freely
    template.yml       # template metadata (jtex spec)
    orcid.svg
{{- end }}
pdfs/                  # output PDFs (gitignored)
```

{{- if eq .Template "lab" }}
## Editing the layout

This project ships a local copy of the `sci-preprint` Typst template at `_templates/paper/`. Edit `_templates/paper/paper.typ` to change fonts, margins, the title block, etc. — your changes apply only to this manuscript. Drop sibling templates (e.g. `_templates/poster/`) in the same folder and reference them from `myst.yml`.
{{- else }}
## Layout

This project uses the `{{.Template}}` MyST template, resolved from the MyST template registry. To switch templates, edit the `template:` field under the typst export in `myst.yml`. To customize layout in-place, run `sci proj new` with `--template lab` to ship an editable local copy.
{{- end }}

## Submission knobs

`myst.yml` lists the toggles for line numbers, anonymization, and title pages. Add a second export entry to produce an anonymous PDF in parallel:

```yaml
- format: typst
{{- if eq .Template "lab" }}
  template: ./_templates/paper
{{- else if ne .Template "default" }}
  template: {{.Template}}
{{- end }}
  output: pdfs/main-anonymous.pdf
  anonymize: true
  title_page: true
```
